08/01/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The parliamentary group of the European Socialist Party (ESP) at the European Parliament convened in Athens on Tuesday (7 January). Greece's ruling party, PASOK, is a member of the ESP. Labour Minister Dimitris Reppas and Finance Minister Nikos Christodoulakis, representing Greece, outlined priorities for the country's term in the rotating EU presidency. (Macedonian Press Agency - 07/01/03)
